Johannesburg A 70-year-old man appeared in Modjadjiskloof Periodical Court on charges of attempted murder, Limpopo police said on Wednesday. Spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said farm owner Michael Toulou allegedly shot a 30-year-old man after accusing him of theft. &quot;The accused allegedly confronted the victim, Simon Mmethi, accusing him of stealing some wood from his farm. He then shot the victim. Mmethi suffered injuries as a result of the shooting and is still in hospital.&quot; The incident took place at Toulou's farm three weeks ago. The court granted him R10 000 bail and postponed the case to March 28. African News Agency